---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<section class="hero">
  <h1>Sync skills, hooks, and instruction files across AI coding agents</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    One source tree, symlinked or copied into Claude Code, Codex, Copilot, Gemini CLI,
    Antigravity, OpenCode, and more. Most agent configs are just plain files, and agentcfg
    manages them as such.
  </p>
  <div class="cta">
    <a class="button" href={`${base}getting-started/installation/`}>Get started</a>
    <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/jorgenosberg/agentcfg">View on GitHub</a>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 5rem auto 3.5rem;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--landing-fg);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .lede {
    color: var(--landing-fg-muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.15rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--landing-btn-bg);
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    background: var(--landing-btn-bg);
    color: var(--landing-btn-fg);
  }

  .button.secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--landing-fg);
    border-color: var(--landing-border);
  }

  .button.secondary:hover {
    border-color: var(--landing-fg-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 40rem) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
